  "description": "These are extensions to the <a href=\"http://zometool.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Zometool</a> system.&nbsp; The struts fit into the pentagonal (red-axis) holes of a standard Zome ball.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe struts are not colored olive when printed.&nbsp; You can paint them with acrylic paints, dye them (if you print in white), or use heat-shrink tubing to achieve certain colors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMany 3D projections of 4D polytopes require olive, lavender, and maroon struts.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe video below describes the general process used to create such models in <a href=\"http://vzome.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">vZome</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;",
